{"id":"339","name":"Out Sick","tagline":"Reschedule your day when you fall sick","icon":"ios12 c3679049983 g59461","latest":"684","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Getting sick is no fun; even worse is interrupting much needed sleep to readjust the next day's schedule when you take a sick day.</p>\n<p>Enter \"Out Sick\", which takes care of all that for you so you can get your rest.</p>\n<p>When run, this shortcut looks at your specified calendars for the current day and:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Emails all attendees of meetings you've scheduled and lets them know you'll need to reschedule.</li>\n<li>Emails all of the meeting owners whose meetings you've accepted and lets them know you can't make it (bonus: each owner gets a single email from you, regardless of how many meetings they have on your calendar).</li>\n<li>Adds a reminder to Reminders for the next day, reminding you to get back to all the missed meetings (a list of which are included in the reminder itself).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You need rest when you're sick; let \"Out Sick\" do the notifying for you.</p>\n<p><strong>UPDATE (2018-10-30):</strong> Today's Shortcuts 2.1 release includes an action to toggle an alarm off, which would be a great addition to this shortcut. However, this action appears to not handle user-specified alarms gracefully. More research is being done.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.5 - Oct. 21, 2018, 8:35 p.m.</strong></p><p>- Added support for multiple calendars!</p>"}